chunk_content: Site (de-identified) and SNU-level results and narratives are posted each quarter for the public to view, download, and analyze through Panorama Spotlight. For more in-depth analyses, partners and stakeholders external to PEPFAR may request access to data for additional PEPFAR data elements. For more specific information around data sharing in PEPFAR, please consult the PEPFAR Data Governance policy. 26 Key Updates and Changes: MER v2.6.1 to MER v2.7 O Through the past several years of quarterly, site-level monitoring, PEPFAR programs have used data to improve patient V outcomes and impact. Changes to the MER guidance highlight key program areas (e.g., index testing services) that should E be taken to scale. Tables 3 and 4 and Figure 11 on the following pages highlight the key details for the MER indicators.
